		<item>
		<title>Luxer 1.0 Release Info and Luxer 2.0 Plan</title>
		<link>http://rmarcus.info/?p=154</link>
		<comments>http://rmarcus.info/?p=154#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 20 Dec 2006 14:12:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ryan Marcus]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Luxer, Battle.net Bot]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://marcusfamily.info/~ryan/blog/?p=173</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Luxer 1.0 is officially done! The only thing preventing me from releasing is the small things I need to do (document, clean forums, get site up, etc.), then, you will all have a working WAR3 bot! Anyhow, I&#8217;d like to announce the official game plan for the next version of Luxer&#8230; 2! Completely redone UI [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Luxer 1.0 is officially done!</p>
<p>The only thing preventing me from releasing is the small things I need to do (document, clean forums, get site up, etc.), then, you will all have a working WAR3 bot!</p>
<p>Anyhow, I&#8217;d like to announce the official game plan for the next version of Luxer&#8230; 2!</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Completely redone UI and code</strong></li>
<p>No more sloppy code, no more sloppy UI. The final Luxer is going to be a shining jewel of the Macintosh, as well as Linux.</p>
<li><strong>Unity</strong></li>
<p>Like all great applications, it is time to add some UNITY to Luxer. My plan is to write a server (called &#8220;UNITY&#8221;) that will allow Luxer users to communicate and share, as well as download trivia questions and upload Chuck Norris jokes. <img src="http://rmarcus.info/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
<li><strong>Custom-Command Access</strong></li>
<p>The main reason I could not get this feature in version 1.0 is because of my own sloppy code. However, in 2, this will not be a problem.</p>
<li><strong>Web Interface&#8230; Batlle.net clans + UNITY = a better battle.net</strong></li>
<p>As a part of UNITY, you will be able to do amazing things with Luxer. A quick brainstorming proposes these features:</p>
<ol>
<li><em>Web-based Chat</em></li>
<p>Get a free hosted, web-based chat room with optional password for your channel.</p>
<li><em>Forum Signatures</em></li>
<p>Now, how is that for sweet? Put your battle.net name, access level, clan channel, and maybe a brief chat history in an image that could become your forum signature.
</ol>
</ul>
<p>There is bound to be tons new in the next version of Luxer, but I will keep it at that for the moment.</p>
<p>There is a small problem with UNITY&#8230; I need somebody to host it. It will be as simple as opening two ports to a computer and running a REALbasic program, but if I could get a Mac or Linux user who is willing to do that, it will save a lot of time. In order for me to use my own server for this, I will have to write the server in Java, which will take, shall we say, years.</p>
<p>So, if you&#8217;ve been too lazy to donate to Luxer, perhaps this is your chance to contribute to the project.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
